1
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:07,879
<i>- Previously on</i> Cross...
Voilà.

2
00:00:07,880 --> 00:00:09,379
None of it matters

3
00:00:09,380 --> 00:00:10,629
without the book.

4
00:00:10,630 --> 00:00:12,719
This is not a scrapbook,
this is his bible.

5
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:13,759
No one

6
00:00:13,760 --> 00:00:15,259
is gonna forget you now.

7
00:00:15,260 --> 00:00:16,849
Drop it.

8
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:19,349
I wanted it to be you, Alex.

9
00:00:19,350 --> 00:00:21,479
Someone from my past is out to get me.

10
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:23,059
<i>In my professional opinion, </i>

11
00:00:23,060 --> 00:00:24,229
<i>she cannot be fixed.</i>

12
00:00:24,230 --> 00:00:26,479
- What's this?
That name you gave us,

13
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:27,729
Peter Lenox.

14
00:00:27,730 --> 00:00:29,569
Go live your life, okay?

15
00:00:29,570 --> 00:00:30,819
Mine's already over.

16
00:00:30,820 --> 00:00:32,739
<i>This guy, he's full of guilt.
He blames himself</i>

17
00:00:32,740 --> 00:00:34,489
<i>for what happened to Deirdre.</i>

18
00:00:34,490 --> 00:00:36,949
Years of focus, years of planning.

19
00:00:36,950 --> 00:00:40,120
<i>A guy like that is never gonna give up.</i>

20
00:00:42,660 --> 00:00:44,960
- Oh, come on. Whoa!

21
00:01:12,740 --> 00:01:15,280
Alex, what are you still doing in bed?

22
00:01:16,610 --> 00:01:18,239
Don't you want to go play with Sampson?

23
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:19,909
He's outside waiting.

24
00:01:19,910 --> 00:01:21,789
I don't feel like it, Nana Mama.

25
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:29,249
I get it.

26
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:33,169
You know, back when I was growing up,
I was terrified of thunderstorms.

27
00:01:33,170 --> 00:01:35,669
Scared the living daylights out of me.

28
00:01:35,670 --> 00:01:39,549
I would hide in my bed just like you
until the storm passed.

29
00:01:39,550 --> 00:01:43,519
But it hasn't been raining out today.

30
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:48,849
No, but you've been through
some real bad storms lately.

31
00:01:48,850 --> 00:01:52,570
Losing your mama? And now your daddy?

32
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:56,699
It's too much for a child.

33
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:59,619
But the thing about storms is,
they don't last forever.

34
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:03,789
And God already gave you
your share, honey.

35
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:07,869
So from now on,
it's only gonna be sunny skies ahead.

36
00:02:07,870 --> 00:02:09,079
Guaranteed.

37
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:11,379
And when the sun is shining?

38
00:02:11,380 --> 00:02:13,339
Oh, that means
it's time to go outside again.

39
00:02:13,340 --> 00:02:16,839
But what if something bad
happens to you, too?

40
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:19,969
I'm not going anywhere, Alex.

41
00:02:19,970 --> 00:02:21,550
Promise?

42
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:24,269
Promise.

43
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:28,939
Got you, Nana.

44
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:30,519
It's gonna be okay, Nana.
It's gonna be okay.

45
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,729
I got you.

46
00:02:31,730 --> 00:02:33,649
I'm gonna get him.

47
00:02:33,650 --> 00:02:34,819
I'm gonna find who did this.

48
00:02:34,820 --> 00:02:37,240
Don't worry, Nana, I'm gonna get him.

49
00:02:38,570 --> 00:02:40,529
Run a FAST. Get her into Bay Three now.

50
00:02:40,530 --> 00:02:41,659
Nana, I'm right here, right here.

51
00:02:41,660 --> 00:02:43,949
Whoa. Only staff past these doors.

52
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:55,549
Daddy!

53
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:57,840
Hey. Hey.

54
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:02,049
Where's Nana Mama? Is she okay?

55
00:03:02,050 --> 00:03:04,009
Doctors say she's stable for now,
but still critical,

56
00:03:04,010 --> 00:03:06,139
so they got to keep an eye on her
to make sure she's okay.

57
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:08,019
Can we see her?

58
00:03:08,020 --> 00:03:11,149
Not yet, baby girl.
They need to run some tests.

59
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:13,229
- I want to see Nana Mama.
Hey, kids.

60
00:03:13,230 --> 00:03:15,069
See that vending machine over there?

61
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:17,479
How about we go find ourselves
some treats?

62
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:19,650
And see if they have anything
Nana would like.

63
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:25,280
Elle, I-I appreciate you coming. When I...

64
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:32,790
She's gonna be okay.

65
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:39,470
Peter did this.

66
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:46,389
The man who's been stalking me.

67
00:03:46,390 --> 00:03:49,059
Now, I got backup coming,
but Damon and Jannie,

68
00:03:49,060 --> 00:03:50,639
they can't go back to the house.

69
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:52,649
I got to get them somewhere safe.

70
00:03:52,650 --> 00:03:54,729
I need to be out looking for him.

71
00:03:54,730 --> 00:03:56,190
They can come home with me.

72
00:03:57,230 --> 00:04:00,779
I-I appreciate that, Elle,
but I don't know where's safe.

73
00:04:00,780 --> 00:04:03,449
This man knows everything about me.

74
00:04:03,450 --> 00:04:07,989
Listen, I-I don't mean to intrude, but...

75
00:04:07,990 --> 00:04:11,119
my family has a cabin out on Goose Creek.

76
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:14,039
And, uh, if you all need
somewhere safe to stay,

77
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:15,539
I could take you up there.

78
00:04:15,540 --> 00:04:17,919
It's nothing fancy,
but it is out of the way.

79
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:22,379
And, uh, it's the last place that anyone
would think of looking for y'all.

80
00:04:22,380 --> 00:04:27,469
Miss Nancy, I hate to suck you into this,
but that would be a lifesaver.

81
00:04:27,470 --> 00:04:32,689
O-Okay, well, it's not you asking,
it's me offering, so...

82
00:04:32,690 --> 00:04:34,599
I'll go.

83
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,559
I could use the time away.

84
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:40,070
Besides, those kids need as many
friendly faces around them as possible.

85
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:43,859
We got Nana Mama's favorite.

86
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:45,360
Red Vines.

87
00:04:46,450 --> 00:04:48,909
Last pack, too. That's good luck, right?

88
00:04:48,910 --> 00:04:51,039
It's got to be.

89
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,829
It'll do you kids good
to get out of the city.

90
00:04:53,830 --> 00:04:56,129
Get a little fresh air, see some nature.

91
00:04:56,130 --> 00:04:58,170
How far away is it?
- Hey.

92
00:04:59,250 --> 00:05:00,799
Goose Creek is out there.

93
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,089
Way out.

94
00:05:02,090 --> 00:05:05,799
I'll bet if you get up early, you could
see families of deer in the forest.

95
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:08,469
Cool. What's the homework policy
while we're out there?

96
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:13,269
homework policy is do it, Miss Thing.

97
00:05:13,270 --> 00:05:14,809
Yeah.

98
00:05:14,810 --> 00:05:16,899
I'll have your teachers
email your assignments.

99
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,809
Oh, actually, um,

100
00:05:18,810 --> 00:05:20,439
I don't have Wi-Fi,

101
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:22,819
and cell service is pretty spotty.

102
00:05:22,820 --> 00:05:24,649
I keep it old-school.

103
00:05:24,650 --> 00:05:26,029
No Internet?

104
00:05:26,030 --> 00:05:28,909
No Internet, but you can call somebody.

105
00:05:28,910 --> 00:05:31,330
Here's the number for the landline.

106
00:05:32,450 --> 00:05:33,410
Thank you. I know

107
00:05:33,411 --> 00:05:34,909
none of this is what you signed up for...

108
00:05:34,910 --> 00:05:38,829
Oh, stop. No, with, with
my own kids grown and gone,

109
00:05:38,830 --> 00:05:41,879
you guys and Regina,
you've become quite the blessing,

110
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:44,259
so I'm, I'm just happy to help.

111
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:46,470
That's very kind of you, Miss Nancy.

112
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:51,640
Before you go, there's something
I want to show you.

113
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:58,059
Is that him?

114
00:05:58,060 --> 00:06:00,400
The man who's been doing all this to us?

115
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:04,779
If you see this man,
I want you to run, okay?

116
00:06:04,780 --> 00:06:07,109
- And get help.
I thought he'd have a scar

117
00:06:07,110 --> 00:06:10,489
on his face or an eyepatch or something.

118
00:06:10,490 --> 00:06:13,909
Hey. Hey.

119
00:06:13,910 --> 00:06:15,829
Everything's gonna be okay.

120
00:06:15,830 --> 00:06:18,460
All right? I promise.

121
00:06:19,710 --> 00:06:22,040
I promise.

122
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:11,929
Detective Cross.

123
00:07:11,930 --> 00:07:14,389
I'm Kat, Peter Lenox's case manager.

124
00:07:14,390 --> 00:07:16,679
Thank you for seeing me
on such short notice.

125
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:19,099
What do you have?
Do you have anything for me?

126
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:21,229
I haven't had valid contact info for him
in nine years, so...

127
00:07:21,230 --> 00:07:22,809
Yeah, that-that figures.

128
00:07:22,810 --> 00:07:24,649
Uh, what about family?
I-I'll take anything. This is urgent.

129
00:07:24,650 --> 00:07:27,319
Uh, based on his records,

130
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:30,649
all his known relatives
are either dead or incarcerated.

131
00:07:30,650 --> 00:07:32,989
What is this about? Is Peter in trouble?

132
00:07:32,990 --> 00:07:34,910
He's terrorizing a family.

133
00:07:35,910 --> 00:07:37,740
My family.

134
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:42,670
I'm sorry.

135
00:07:43,710 --> 00:07:45,669
Okay, this wouldn't be in his file

136
00:07:45,670 --> 00:07:48,919
and it-it's probably not helpful,
but, uh...

137
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:50,719
I remember Peter had a "street mom."

138
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:53,549
Lady who'd come in with him sometimes,
help him with the paperwork.

139
00:07:53,550 --> 00:07:55,179
Not a relative?

140
00:07:55,180 --> 00:07:57,599
Peter called her his "fairy godmother."

141
00:07:57,600 --> 00:08:01,269
Sweet lady.
And, uh, there was someone else, too.

142
00:08:01,270 --> 00:08:03,729
White girl with dark hair.
What was her name?

143
00:08:03,730 --> 00:08:05,769
It was like Dee Dee?
Something like that?

144
00:08:05,770 --> 00:08:07,939
- Deirdre.
- Deirdre, yeah.

145
00:08:07,940 --> 00:08:09,649
She's in jail, though.

146
00:08:09,650 --> 00:08:11,279
- Street mom.
- Mm-hmm.

147
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:13,199
- How can I find her?
- I couldn't tell you that.

148
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:16,659
She never applied for benefits herself,
so she's not in the system.

149
00:08:16,660 --> 00:08:18,119
Not even a name. I'm so sorry.

150
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:21,409
Yeah, well, just thank you,
thank you for your time.

151
00:08:21,410 --> 00:08:24,879
Look, if you think of anything else at
all, just anything, you-you let me know.

152
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:26,380
Yeah.

153
00:08:33,470 --> 00:08:35,759
It's so beautiful out here.

154
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:38,309
So calm, so quiet.

155
00:08:38,310 --> 00:08:39,849
Yeah.

156
00:08:39,850 --> 00:08:42,599
It was my little girl's favorite place.

157
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,849
Been in my family for years.

158
00:08:44,850 --> 00:08:47,439
No matter how bad things got,

159
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:49,689
this place was always a refuge.

160
00:08:49,690 --> 00:08:52,399
I sleep like a baby out here.

161
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:54,399
Mm-mm. I'm used to the city.

162
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,109
I mean,

163
00:08:56,110 --> 00:08:59,619
the country quiet, I can't sleep a wink.

164
00:08:59,620 --> 00:09:01,539
Oh, girl, my son, too.

165
00:09:01,540 --> 00:09:05,709
Look in the medicine cabinet,
you will find what you need.

166
00:09:05,710 --> 00:09:08,839
- And then you can sleep like a baby, too.

167
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,379
Do you have a dog?

168
00:09:10,380 --> 00:09:11,839
Oh, my kids did.

169
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,299
Yeah.

170
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,799
Passed away a while back.

171
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:16,799
Kept the leash, though.

172
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:18,889
I guess some things
are just hard to let go of.

173
00:09:18,890 --> 00:09:20,719
What's this for?

174
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:22,059
- Baby, do not touch that.

175
00:09:22,060 --> 00:09:23,679
Mosquitoes.

176
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:26,519
You can take out a whole swarm
with just one pull of that trigger,

177
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:29,979
which is why it is not safe for children.

178
00:09:31,230 --> 00:09:32,689
We might need it to protect ourselves.

179
00:09:32,690 --> 00:09:34,949
Damon, you don't got
to worry about that.

180
00:09:34,950 --> 00:09:36,950
Nobody bad gonna find us out here.

181
00:09:37,990 --> 00:09:40,529
Why does that man hate us?

182
00:09:40,530 --> 00:09:43,120
- I don't know, baby.
- I guess...

183
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:48,669
...sometimes some people hurt
so bad inside,

184
00:09:48,670 --> 00:09:51,750
they just want everybody else
to hurt, too.

185
00:09:53,550 --> 00:09:55,169
Aw. Okay, enough of that.

186
00:09:55,170 --> 00:09:56,759
Who wants hot chocolate?

187
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:59,470
- Yes! Yes, yes, yes.

188
00:10:48,980 --> 00:10:50,059
- I think that's exactly...
Hey.

189
00:10:50,060 --> 00:10:51,229
Hey.
- Heard y'all helping Cross

190
00:10:51,230 --> 00:10:52,689
track down Peter Lenox.

191
00:10:52,690 --> 00:10:55,149
- Yeah, everybody is.
- Any luck?

192
00:10:55,150 --> 00:10:57,739
Not yet. It's just a matter of time.

193
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:58,989
Oh, that's good.

194
00:10:58,990 --> 00:11:00,199
What about the kids?

195
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,739
- They all right?
- Yeah.

196
00:11:01,740 --> 00:11:05,579
He sent 'em off to stay with a family
friend until we get Peter locked up.

197
00:11:05,580 --> 00:11:08,249
We're all just hoping Nana Mama
pulls through.

198
00:11:08,250 --> 00:11:10,329
Yeah. Yeah, me, too.

199
00:11:10,330 --> 00:11:12,709
I just got back from the hospital, so...

200
00:11:12,710 --> 00:11:15,750
It's not good, but she's a fighter, so...

201
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:18,919
Look, if y'all need any help,
just let me know.

202
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:20,340
Should we tell Cross to call you?

203
00:11:21,470 --> 00:11:24,180
No. If he wants to, he will.

204
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,940
- Oh. Thanks, Tana.
- You're welcome.

205
00:11:37,110 --> 00:11:40,899
Hey, Alex, what's up
with you and Two John?

206
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,319
What do you mean? Did he say something?

207
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:46,789
He was in here earlier,
I asked where you were, he didn't know.

208
00:11:46,790 --> 00:11:50,619
And that's the first time he's ever
not known, as far as when I ask.

209
00:11:50,620 --> 00:11:54,539
I thought of the worst thing
I could say to John,

210
00:11:54,540 --> 00:11:56,589
and I said it.

211
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:59,919
And then you apologized?

212
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:04,260
Yeah, I don't think sorry's
gonna change anything.

213
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:08,220
You might be right. I just...

214
00:12:10,060 --> 00:12:12,810
If it was me, I would find out.

215
00:12:31,660 --> 00:12:32,869
<i>Hello?</i>

216
00:12:32,870 --> 00:12:35,129
Miss Nancy. It's Alex.

217
00:12:35,130 --> 00:12:38,419
I was just checking to make sure
you guys are all settled in all right.

218
00:12:38,420 --> 00:12:42,129
Oh, yeah. Snug as bugs in a rug.

219
00:12:42,130 --> 00:12:44,219
Um, but I'm really glad you called,

220
00:12:44,220 --> 00:12:47,299
because Elle and the kids were
starting to get a bit worried.

221
00:12:47,300 --> 00:12:51,849
Um, were you able to track down that man?

222
00:12:51,850 --> 00:12:54,689
No, not yet.
Hey, can I speak to Elle for a sec?

223
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:55,980
<i>Sure. Elle.</i>

224
00:12:57,060 --> 00:12:58,690
Thank you.

225
00:13:02,070 --> 00:13:05,779
You just interrupted
a very competitive game of Life.

226
00:13:05,780 --> 00:13:09,409
These kids of yours,
they gonna run the world one day.

227
00:13:09,410 --> 00:13:12,200
Yeah, that sounds like
my Damon and Jannie.

228
00:13:13,290 --> 00:13:16,829
Hey, um, any updates on Nana Mama?

229
00:13:16,830 --> 00:13:20,459
Yeah, she's, uh, she's stable,
but there's some internal bleeding.

230
00:13:20,460 --> 00:13:23,969
<i>And they can't fix her until
they get that under control.</i>

231
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:25,929
She's gonna make it, Alex.

232
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:28,179
I know it.

233
00:13:28,180 --> 00:13:30,719
If that's Daddy, I need to speak
to him right this minute, please.

234
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:33,099
Hold on.

235
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:35,939
Daddy, the cabin is so cool.

236
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:38,019
There's a fireplace and bunk beds,

237
00:13:38,020 --> 00:13:40,269
<i>and it's okay if me and Damon
both want the top bunk</i>

238
00:13:40,270 --> 00:13:42,649
<i>- because Elle said we could take turns.</i>
- Yeah?

239
00:13:42,650 --> 00:13:44,399
And Auntie Nancy gave us chores
and said she'll pay us.

240
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:47,489
Oh, it's "Auntie" now, huh?

241
00:13:47,490 --> 00:13:49,409
Yeah. It was Damon's idea,

242
00:13:49,410 --> 00:13:52,039
but Miss Nancy said
she would like it if we called her that.

243
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:54,159
She says what makes you family
isn't blood.

244
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:55,909
It's how much you love each other.

245
00:13:55,910 --> 00:13:58,749
So people like her
and Uncle John are family, too, right?

246
00:13:58,750 --> 00:14:01,840
That's right, kiddo.
You don't have to be blood to be family.

247
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:04,550
<i>Blood doesn't make you family.</i>

248
00:14:06,340 --> 00:14:08,090
<i>Blood doesn't make you family.</i>

249
00:14:09,970 --> 00:14:11,299
<i>Blood doesn't make you family.</i>

250
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:13,099
<i>Daddy? You still there?</i>

251
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:16,309
Yeah, yeah. Yeah, I'm here. Uh...

252
00:14:16,310 --> 00:14:18,599
Hey, you kiss Damon for me, okay?

253
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:22,069
I am not kissing Damon,
but I'll tell him you said hi.

254
00:14:22,070 --> 00:14:23,229
<i>Love you.</i>

255
00:14:23,230 --> 00:14:24,990
Love you, too, baby.

256
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:33,539
Alex. Cross.

257
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:36,619
Hey, I don't have time
for anything right now.

258
00:14:36,620 --> 00:14:39,869
You don't know what this is about.

259
00:14:39,870 --> 00:14:42,169
Ramsey sent me his book.

260
00:14:42,170 --> 00:14:45,259
- What are you gonna do with it?
- I don't know.

261
00:14:45,260 --> 00:14:48,049
I mean, I-I have a million things
in my mind.

262
00:14:48,050 --> 00:14:51,009
Tania, I don't have time
to help you right now. I don't.

263
00:14:51,010 --> 00:14:52,549
Shit.

264
00:14:52,550 --> 00:14:54,889
Something's really going on. What is it?

265
00:14:54,890 --> 00:14:57,229
If you want to hold onto that
for a couple days, we can talk about it.

266
00:14:57,230 --> 00:15:00,810
Otherwise, please don't make him a star.

267
00:15:05,690 --> 00:15:06,739
<i>You lost your mother.</i>

268
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:08,739
<i>How did it feel to lose a family member?</i>

269
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:10,699
<i>Blood doesn't
make you family.</i>

270
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:15,160
<i>What makes you family
is how much people love you.</i>

271
00:15:17,870 --> 00:15:21,460
<i>What makes you family
is how much people love you.</i>

272
00:15:25,050 --> 00:15:28,510
<i>What makes you family
is how much people love you.</i>

273
00:15:37,310 --> 00:15:38,639
You'll never find me.

274
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:41,519
One Mississippi, two Mississippi,

275
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:44,399
three Mississippi, four Mississippi,

276
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:47,859
five Mississippi, six Mississippi,

277
00:15:47,860 --> 00:15:49,859
seven Mississippi...

278
00:15:49,860 --> 00:15:51,609
The woman who helped Peter
with his housing application,

279
00:15:51,610 --> 00:15:53,409
<i>would you remember her face
if you saw it again?</i>

280
00:15:53,410 --> 00:15:55,369
Yeah, I think so.

281
00:15:55,370 --> 00:15:57,740
I'm sending you a link.

282
00:16:21,020 --> 00:16:23,850
<i>Did you get it?</i>
- Internet comes and goes around here.

283
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:28,189
<i>Got it.</i>

284
00:16:28,190 --> 00:16:29,979
Is that the woman you saw?

285
00:16:29,980 --> 00:16:32,859
Ah. Y-Yeah, that's her.

286
00:16:32,860 --> 00:16:35,239
<i>Uh, she's aged a little bit, </i>

287
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:38,029
<i>but that is definitely
Peter Lenox's street mom.</i>

288
00:16:38,030 --> 00:16:39,989
<i>This is crazy.</i>

289
00:16:39,990 --> 00:16:41,580
<i>How did you figure that out?</i>

290
00:16:55,970 --> 00:16:57,930
What you doing?

291
00:16:59,310 --> 00:17:01,269
Miss Nancy. We were playing.

292
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:02,429
Hide and seek.

293
00:17:02,430 --> 00:17:05,150
I thought this
would be a good space to hide.

294
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:09,940
Not good enough to stop me
from finding you.

295
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:15,609
All right, come on up, wash your hands.

296
00:17:15,610 --> 00:17:17,530
It's almost time for dinner.

297
00:17:36,890 --> 00:17:38,680
Damon, baby, you okay?

298
00:17:42,770 --> 00:17:45,139
You kids are under a lot of stress.

299
00:17:45,140 --> 00:17:47,349
I hope this ends soon.

300
00:17:47,350 --> 00:17:49,689
Oh. Knowing Alex, I'm sure it will.

301
00:17:49,690 --> 00:17:51,570
And in the meantime...

302
00:17:52,690 --> 00:17:55,699
...there's nothing to worry about.

303
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:58,109
We're all alone out here.

304
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:02,870
- Excuse me.
- Mm-hmm.

305
00:18:05,330 --> 00:18:06,619
Hello?

306
00:18:06,620 --> 00:18:08,419
<i>Hey, Miss Nancy,
um, I'm sorry to bother you again, </i>

307
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:11,129
but, uh, can I talk to Elle for a sec?

308
00:18:11,130 --> 00:18:15,339
Um, Elle is just bundling up the kids,

309
00:18:15,340 --> 00:18:17,339
because we're gonna go out back
to make s'mores.

310
00:18:17,340 --> 00:18:19,179
<i>Let me give her a message.</i>

311
00:18:19,180 --> 00:18:21,049
No, uh, you know what,
it'll only take a minute,

312
00:18:21,050 --> 00:18:22,929
