313
00:18:22,930 --> 00:18:24,599
<i>It's kind of important.</i>

314
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:25,930
Oh, is something wrong?

315
00:18:28,810 --> 00:18:30,399
No, uh...

316
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:35,439
No, no, it's, um, Jannie, she-she has
a little condition, and I just realized

317
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:37,699
<i>I forgot to send up the medicine, so...</i>

318
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:39,569
<i>But now-now there's a way to manage it</i>

319
00:18:39,570 --> 00:18:42,159
without the medicine, and-and I need
to walk Elle through the regimen.

320
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:46,909
All that time that I spent at the house,
I never saw Jannie take any medicine.

321
00:18:46,910 --> 00:18:49,459
<i>And Regina certainly didn't
mention anything.</i>

322
00:18:49,460 --> 00:18:53,339
I'm surprised that it never came up,
but it is a thing, so...

323
00:18:53,340 --> 00:18:56,209
<i>can I please talk to Elle?</i>

324
00:18:56,210 --> 00:18:58,679
Is it a thing, Alex?

325
00:19:01,050 --> 00:19:02,970
Or do you know?

326
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:05,219
I'm sorry?

327
00:19:05,220 --> 00:19:08,389
<i>Do you know who I am?</i>

328
00:19:08,390 --> 00:19:10,810
<i>Do you know what this is?</i>

329
00:19:12,610 --> 00:19:15,479
Do not hurt my children. Do you hear me?

330
00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:17,899
<i>Aw.</i>

331
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:22,279
I love that "I'm in charge" tone you got.

332
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:25,659
<i>But I don't think
that's your reality right now, is it?</i>

333
00:19:25,660 --> 00:19:27,789
Look, if you touch one hair
on their heads,

334
00:19:27,790 --> 00:19:29,909
- I swear...
<i>- Jannie? Jannie.</i>

335
00:19:29,910 --> 00:19:31,249
Honey. Come here for a minute.

336
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:33,669
Hey.

337
00:19:33,670 --> 00:19:37,549
<i>You know what? Um, I just remembered
there's a special place</i>

338
00:19:37,550 --> 00:19:39,129
that I wanted to show you.

339
00:19:39,130 --> 00:19:40,969
It was my little girl's favorite.

340
00:19:40,970 --> 00:19:42,679
<i>I think you're really gonna like it, too.</i>

341
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:45,720
<i>What is it?
- No, it's a surprise.</i>

342
00:19:58,780 --> 00:20:00,069
Oh, my God.

343
00:20:00,070 --> 00:20:01,399
She's his mother?

344
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,739
What are we gonna do?

345
00:20:02,740 --> 00:20:05,069
Well, how about

346
00:20:05,070 --> 00:20:08,909
we take a walk in the forest,
just you and me?

347
00:20:08,910 --> 00:20:10,749
- No.
<i>That sounds like fun.</i>

348
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:12,459
<i>Mm-hmm.
Can we do it after the s'mores?</i>

349
00:20:12,460 --> 00:20:14,999
Absolutely, we can do it
after the s'mores.

350
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,090
Okay, go back. Finish your dinner.

351
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:22,179
- What's wrong?
- Nothing.

352
00:20:22,180 --> 00:20:24,179
Can you just go get more butter, please?

353
00:20:24,180 --> 00:20:26,509
Yes. Thank you. Thank you, baby.

354
00:20:26,510 --> 00:20:28,770
O... kay.

355
00:20:31,270 --> 00:20:33,189
- Should we tell her?
- No.

356
00:20:33,190 --> 00:20:36,399
No. And I can't have you acting
any different, Damon.

357
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:38,269
I need you to do something for me.

358
00:20:38,270 --> 00:20:39,649
Can you get Miss Nancy's keys?

359
00:20:39,650 --> 00:20:40,989
Good.

360
00:20:40,990 --> 00:20:43,029
I will handle everything else.

361
00:20:43,030 --> 00:20:45,619
<i>Please.
Please, please, </i>

362
00:20:45,620 --> 00:20:47,869
please don't hurt my children.

363
00:20:47,870 --> 00:20:50,869
Now, that's a much more
appropriate tone, Alex.

364
00:20:50,870 --> 00:20:54,869
<i>I know that everybody thinks
that you're the world's best detective, </i>

365
00:20:54,870 --> 00:20:58,750
but to me you're just
another little fuckboy.

366
00:21:00,170 --> 00:21:02,799
<i>Why-why-why are you doing this?</i>

367
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:05,089
<i>You're such an expert, </i>

368
00:21:05,090 --> 00:21:06,679
