459
00:27:27,850 --> 00:27:30,060
See you on the other side.

460
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:07,139
- Show me.
- I'm not armed.

461
00:28:07,140 --> 00:28:09,019
Where are they?

462
00:28:09,020 --> 00:28:10,890
You want to see your kids or not?

463
00:28:42,170 --> 00:28:44,680
Alex.

464
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:47,049
They're fine...

465
00:28:47,050 --> 00:28:49,060
for now.

466
00:28:52,810 --> 00:28:54,190
Put 'em on.

467
00:29:00,610 --> 00:29:02,530
Sit down.

468
00:29:03,650 --> 00:29:04,820
Nuh-uh.

469
00:29:07,410 --> 00:29:09,080
Chair by the window.

470
00:29:22,470 --> 00:29:25,179
I tried to get them out.

471
00:29:25,180 --> 00:29:27,430
I'm sorry I got you into this.

472
00:30:24,190 --> 00:30:27,859
You asking
the wrong questions, Alex.

473
00:30:27,860 --> 00:30:30,069
This is about you, not those kids.

474
00:30:30,070 --> 00:30:31,529
Then why are they here?

475
00:30:31,530 --> 00:30:32,989
Damon and Jannie didn't do anything...

476
00:30:32,990 --> 00:30:35,960
Deirdre didn't do anything.

477
00:30:37,040 --> 00:30:39,329
But you said she was crazy.

478
00:30:39,330 --> 00:30:42,339
You said she couldn't be fixed.

479
00:30:42,340 --> 00:30:45,509
By the time I met her, she was broken.

480
00:30:45,510 --> 00:30:49,799
But I should never have said
that she couldn't be fixed. I'm sorry.

481
00:30:49,800 --> 00:30:52,049
- I am, Miss Nancy.

482
00:30:52,050 --> 00:30:55,219
Wouldn't that be nice
if "sorry" was all I wanted?

483
00:30:55,220 --> 00:30:57,809
Was there something else? Huh?

484
00:30:57,810 --> 00:30:59,269
Hmm? Just go ahead,
t-tell-tell me what it is.

485
00:30:59,270 --> 00:31:01,980
Why you keep looking at your watch?
You got somewhere to be?

486
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:06,440
He brought backup.

487
00:31:07,700 --> 00:31:10,070
Just like you said he would.

488
00:31:12,450 --> 00:31:13,620
Your buddy's dead, Cross.

489
00:31:16,750 --> 00:31:20,039
Bleeding out on the forest floor
like a stag.

490
00:31:20,040 --> 00:31:21,829
- No.

491
00:31:21,830 --> 00:31:23,090
Maybe go back later...

492
00:31:24,250 --> 00:31:25,379
...collect the antlers.

493
00:31:25,380 --> 00:31:26,509
No.

494
00:31:26,510 --> 00:31:28,260
No.

495
00:31:33,510 --> 00:31:35,010
Alex!

496
00:31:36,020 --> 00:31:38,309
I've wanted to do this
for so fucking long.

497
00:31:38,310 --> 00:31:40,479
Peter, stop.

498
00:31:40,480 --> 00:31:42,649
That's not the plan anymore.

499
00:31:42,650 --> 00:31:43,770
Give me that.

500
00:31:45,110 --> 00:31:46,359
Take this.

501
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:48,650
And get him back in the chair.

502
00:32:01,370 --> 00:32:03,289
So, Alex,

503
00:32:03,290 --> 00:32:06,669
you've lost your wife,

504
00:32:06,670 --> 00:32:08,669
lost your best friend.

505
00:32:08,670 --> 00:32:12,009
Grandma's barely alive.

506
00:32:12,010 --> 00:32:14,800
Mm-mm. You still don't hurt like I do.

507
00:32:17,350 --> 00:32:22,099
You still don't know
what it's like to lose a child.

508
00:32:22,100 --> 00:32:23,189
What?

509
00:32:23,190 --> 00:32:25,309
Oh, my God. Please, Miss Nancy, please...

510
00:32:25,310 --> 00:32:27,820
Shut the fuck up.

511
