who, uh, made a mistake and,

564
00:35:09,270 --> 00:35:11,899
and, uh, and got scared,

565
00:35:11,900 --> 00:35:14,979
and things got out of control.

566
00:35:14,980 --> 00:35:17,779
Jury would never go hard
on someone like that.

567
00:35:17,780 --> 00:35:20,029
She might even be out in a year.

568
00:35:20,030 --> 00:35:21,699
Maybe even less.

569
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:22,950
Okay.

570
00:35:25,240 --> 00:35:27,869
Yeah, I'll do it.

571
00:35:27,870 --> 00:35:29,249
He's my brother, I-I have to.

572
00:35:29,250 --> 00:35:31,540
Oh, God. Thank you.

573
00:35:33,040 --> 00:35:37,050
What makes you family is
how much people love you.

574
00:35:40,300 --> 00:35:43,139
Peter, she never told you.

575
00:35:43,140 --> 00:35:45,809
Your mother's the reason
Deirdre went to prison.

576
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:48,389
- It's a lie. It's a lie.
- What's he talking about?

577
00:35:48,390 --> 00:35:50,979
I read the letters
between you and Deirdre.

578
00:35:50,980 --> 00:35:54,769
I saw you racked with guilt,
knowing she went to prison...

579
