764
00:47:53,830 --> 00:47:56,659
So you are running for mayor.

765
00:47:56,660 --> 00:48:01,039
And me not facing
a disciplinary panel probably helps.

766
00:48:01,040 --> 00:48:03,789
Well, sure, it helps me,
and you get a do-over.

767
00:48:03,790 --> 00:48:05,379
But you earned it.

768
00:48:05,380 --> 00:48:07,589
That's not the world I want to live in.

769
00:48:07,590 --> 00:48:10,629
But you do. That's the reality,

770
00:48:10,630 --> 00:48:12,799
whether you're on the job or not.

771
00:48:12,800 --> 00:48:16,060
And if you're not, how are you
ever going to change things?

772
00:48:18,680 --> 00:48:20,560
You're a hero, Alex.

773
00:48:21,640 --> 00:48:24,480
But only you get to decide
what that means.

774
00:48:48,050 --> 00:48:49,759
Look, I don't know if they told you,

775
00:48:49,760 --> 00:48:52,009
but this is a spit-free zone.

776
00:48:52,010 --> 00:48:54,179
As a matter of fact, I got a whole
circumference around me

777
00:48:54,180 --> 00:48:56,550
that needs to stay
saliva-free at all times.

778
00:48:57,640 --> 00:49:00,059
I got a call to come get
Emir's personal effects.

779
00:49:03,140 --> 00:49:04,439
Evidence is downstairs.

780
00:49:04,440 --> 00:49:05,519
I know.

781
00:49:05,520 --> 00:49:07,400
I, um...

782
00:49:09,070 --> 00:49:10,689
...I came to say thank you.

783
00:49:10,690 --> 00:49:11,779
Hold up.

784
00:49:11,780 --> 00:49:14,860
Are we having
a civil conversation, Malika?

785
00:49:18,200 --> 00:49:20,120
You still ain't shit.

786
00:49:28,630 --> 00:49:30,670
Better watch yourself, girl.

787
00:49:53,400 --> 00:49:55,279
Thank you for coming.

788
00:49:55,280 --> 00:49:57,660
I'm not here for you.

789
00:50:02,830 --> 00:50:03,999
<i>Why'd you do it?</i>

790
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:05,079
Why me?

791
00:50:05,080 --> 00:50:06,459
My wife was murdered

792
00:50:06,460 --> 00:50:08,129
near Union Market.

793
00:50:08,130 --> 00:50:11,090
You were the only employee
with a violent crime on his record.

794
00:50:12,670 --> 00:50:14,419
You had called sick that day,

795
00:50:14,420 --> 00:50:15,929
and the killer,

796
00:50:15,930 --> 00:50:18,219
they'd used your security badge

797
00:50:18,220 --> 00:50:21,259
to escape through the delivery tunnels.

798
00:50:21,260 --> 00:50:22,889
I reported that badge stolen.

799
00:50:22,890 --> 00:50:24,559
I know that now,

800
00:50:24,560 --> 00:50:27,099
but at the time
I figured either you-you...

801
00:50:27,100 --> 00:50:30,189
you killed her or you knew who did.

802
00:50:30,190 --> 00:50:32,400
- He didn't know shit.
Please let him get it out.

803
00:50:37,030 --> 00:50:39,159
And when you started running, I...

804
00:50:39,160 --> 00:50:41,329
Damn right, I took off, man.

805
00:50:41,330 --> 00:50:43,039
You think I don't know what it means

806
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:44,869
when a cop shows up out of the blue?

807
00:50:46,120 --> 00:50:48,789
Don't even need a record.

808
00:50:48,790 --> 00:50:50,539
Don't need shit.

809
00:50:50,540 --> 00:50:52,670
Just the color of my skin.

810
00:50:53,760 --> 00:50:55,720
The color of our skin.

811
00:50:57,760 --> 00:51:00,139
You been on the job so long,
you forgot what you look like?

812
00:51:00,140 --> 00:51:02,099
No, I haven't.

813
00:51:02,100 --> 00:51:04,219
Then you need to act like it, man.

814
00:51:04,220 --> 00:51:06,559
You're absolutely right,

815
00:51:06,560 --> 00:51:10,900
and I am so, so sorry.

816
00:51:18,780 --> 00:51:20,280
You should resubmit your complaint.

817
00:51:21,950 --> 00:51:25,699
Publicly, so the department
can't sweep it under the rug.

818
00:51:25,700 --> 00:51:27,459
I don't need your badge.

819
00:51:27,460 --> 00:51:30,749
Just want cops to live by
the same rules as the rest of us.

820
00:51:30,750 --> 00:51:33,039
But the next time

821
00:51:33,040 --> 00:51:34,459
you see a brother running,

822
00:51:34,460 --> 00:51:36,459
I hope you put yourself between him

823
00:51:36,460 --> 00:51:38,840
and whatever the fuck is about to happen.

824
00:51:39,970 --> 00:51:41,390
I will.

825
00:51:42,390 --> 00:51:44,100
I promise you.

826
00:52:08,700 --> 00:52:10,000
Let's go, Damon!

827
00:52:40,280 --> 00:52:44,369
You got this,
you got this.

828
00:52:44,370 --> 00:52:45,990
You got this.

829
00:54:14,830 --> 00:54:16,169
I'll be right back.

830
00:54:37,980 --> 00:54:40,690
So, you're here.

831
00:54:42,360 --> 00:54:45,190
What should we talk about?

832
00:54:52,450 --> 00:54:54,330
Maria.

833
00:55:09,430 --> 00:55:10,340
<i>So, </i>

834
00:55:10,341 --> 00:55:13,719
Crossy-Cross really thinking
he can pin me as the Fanboy?

835
00:55:13,720 --> 00:55:15,349
Maybe not forever.

836
00:55:15,350 --> 00:55:16,929
He is planning on

837
00:55:16,930 --> 00:55:19,230
using that book to make you
America's most wanted.

838
00:55:20,980 --> 00:55:22,359
But he did build you an escape hatch.

839
00:55:22,360 --> 00:55:25,569
He knows you killed Tavio Lemmons
and Vanessa Norris.

840
00:55:25,570 --> 00:55:28,820
Knowing... ain't proving.

841
00:55:29,910 --> 00:55:31,069
It's Cross.

842
00:55:31,070 --> 00:55:32,159
You want to roll the dice?

843
00:55:32,160 --> 00:55:34,829
I want to hear the offer.

844
00:55:34,830 --> 00:55:36,580
That's fair.

845
00:55:37,960 --> 00:55:39,419
Well, a lot of Ramsey's victims

846
00:55:39,420 --> 00:55:41,419
have family members
that are still looking for answers,

847
00:55:41,420 --> 00:55:43,289
and that's where you come in.

848
00:55:43,290 --> 00:55:45,089
You would have to
provide us with information

849
00:55:45,090 --> 00:55:46,759
that would lead directly to
the recovery and positive ID

850
00:55:46,760 --> 00:55:49,969
of at least six Fanboy victims.

851
00:55:49,970 --> 00:55:51,679
Think you can do that?

852
00:55:51,680 --> 00:55:53,299
In return for?

853
00:55:53,300 --> 00:55:54,719
Full immunity,

854
00:55:54,720 --> 00:55:56,810
with 24 months served.

855
00:55:59,190 --> 00:56:03,519
You have any idea how long
24 months is in dog years?

856
00:56:03,520 --> 00:56:06,149
Come on, I hate math.

857
00:56:06,150 --> 00:56:08,860
I am guessing it's less than life.

858
00:56:12,910 --> 00:56:15,489
I get that immunity in writing,

859
00:56:15,490 --> 00:56:18,199
and you can tell Crossy-Cross
we got a deal.

860
00:56:18,200 --> 00:56:20,920
I'll turn myself in tomorrow at 10:00.

861
00:56:23,750 --> 00:56:25,459
Today.

862
00:56:25,460 --> 00:56:27,510
When you're done eating.

863
00:56:30,970 --> 00:56:34,969
That puts a different spin
on these here wings,

864
00:56:34,970 --> 00:56:36,720
- but okay.
- Okay.

865
00:56:40,310 --> 00:56:41,809
One more thing.

866
00:56:41,810 --> 00:56:43,229
It'd be nice

867
00:56:43,230 --> 00:56:44,439
to have some money waiting for you

868
00:56:44,440 --> 00:56:47,149
- when you got out, wouldn't it?

869
00:56:47,150 --> 00:56:48,779
Now, you see, you see.

870
00:56:48,780 --> 00:56:51,450
I knew you had your own angle. What it be?

871
00:56:53,200 --> 00:56:55,529
Ramsey had a lot of dirt
on people worth having dirt on.

872
00:56:55,530 --> 00:56:57,239
Yes, yes, yes. Yes, he did.

873
00:56:57,240 --> 00:56:58,949
And if I knew where it was,

874
00:56:58,950 --> 00:57:02,039
why wouldn't I keep
all that dirt for myself?

875
00:57:02,040 --> 00:57:05,129
If you want to work all those
Capitol Hill assholes retail, sure.

876
00:57:05,130 --> 00:57:09,459
But I suspect you'd much rather
get paid wholesale and just walk away.

877
00:57:09,460 --> 00:57:13,969
Is this you or... our Uncle Sam talking?

878
00:57:13,970 --> 00:57:16,760
Money won't know where it came from.

879
00:57:19,140 --> 00:57:22,390
I guess data is the new oil.
